<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-18T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="17" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Permanent Disarmament
                                Commission/92: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-18T18:00:00+01:00">February 18, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received February 18—1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>980. Bourquin Committee met this afternoon and postponed discussion
                                of Soviet proposal for a permanent peace conference until the
                                American draft (chapter 4) has been studied. Articles 17, 18, 19,
                                34, 35, 36, 37 have been selected for preliminary discussion while
                                the others are reserved until further progress has been made in the
                                other committees.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>